description:
&lt;p&gt;Our nationwide emotional wellbeing team currently have an opportunity for a Cognitive Behavioural Therapist. Start your journey with us whilst we’ll support you to be your best.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Cognitive Behavioural Therapist, you will provide private sector clients with high quality Cognitive Behavioural Therapy. Your referrals will come from all kinds of sources – from GP’s to insurance companies. Patients will rely on you for assessment and treatment, either as stand-alone therapy or part of a more comprehensive package of vocational rehabilitation care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based at one or more of our Nuffield Health locations, you will practice semi-autonomously, delivering therapy in a range of different clinics and locations. You will enjoy excellent support from a dedicated administration team, based at our Telford office. We will provide a generous mileage allowance for your visits to clients and to attend regular team days. What’s more, we offer an annual contribution of £500 for continuous professional development after a qualifying period (pro-rata for part time employees) .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Person&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To succeed as a Cognitive Behavioural Therapist you will;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Have, or be close to completing, your BABCP, BACP, COSCA or other appropriate accrediting body with a postgraduate diploma in CBT (or equivalent) as our minimum requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Be highly organised and be a supportive member of our CBT network.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Have excellent communication skills and really focus on your customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return, we offer a working environment that will help you grow your skills and experience and get the best out of life. Other benefits include 25 days’ annual holiday (increasing with service), gym membership, private healthcare and a range of lifestyle and financial wellbeing benefits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Be your best and join us in building a healthier nation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary - Up to £39,000 per annum (Dependant on Experience)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date - 16/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location - Oxford&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contract Type - Permanent &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full or Part-timeroles available (working on a roster basis between&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;7.30am to 7.30pm&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Applications will be considered as they are received and interviews will be arranged accordingly. We reserve the right to close adverts early, for example, where we have received an unprecedented high volume of applications. Therefore please apply early to ensure you are considered for the post.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
